results.name: Triangle T(n,k) giving number of 3 X k polyominoes with n cells (n >= 3, 1<=k<=n-2).
comment: Note that for k=3 (polyominoes with square bounding rectangle) these are not the free polyominoes, because Read does not apply the full symmetry group of order 8 to reduce the fixed polyominoes for c_q(n), but only the symmetry group of order 4 (excluding the 90 deg rotations). The free polyominoes with square bounding rectangles are the z_3(n) instead. - _R. J. Mathar_, May 12 2019
link: R. C. Read, Contributions to the cell growth problem, Canad. J. Math., 14 (1962), 1-20.
